    "causal_summary": "When running `/spec_kit:deep-review` or `/spec_kit:deep-research` on a child phase inside a parent spec tree, both skills create their output folders (`review/`, `research/`) **inside the child phase folder**. In a spec tree with many nested phases (like `026-graph-and-context-optimization` with 14 phases, some 3-4 levels deep), this scatters review and research artifacts across dozens of nested directories. Finding a specific review requires knowing the exact nesting path. Manual consolidation after the fact (as we did for 026 -- moving 42 review + 18 research folders) is tedious and error-prone.",
